ZEQ2-Lite
Open-sourced and mod expandable project based on a highly modified ioQuake3 engine foundation and features many true-to-reference DBZ visuals and mechanics. Developer sandbox for people who want to tinker with basic game development.

173  if ( tr.currentModel->numLods < 2 )
174  {
175  // model has only 1 LOD level, skip computations and bias
176  lod = 0;
177  }
178  else
179  {
180  // multiple LODs exist, so compute projected bounding sphere
181  // and use that as a criteria for selecting LOD
182  frame = ( md3Frame_t * ) ( ( ( unsigned char * ) tr.currentModel->md3[0] ) + tr.currentModel->md3[0]->ofsFrames );
183 
184  frame += ent->e.frame;
185 
186  radius = RadiusFromBounds( frame->bounds[0], frame->bounds[1] );
187 
188 
189  if ( ( projectedRadius = ProjectRadius( radius, ent->e.origin ) ) != 0 )
190  {
191  lodscale = r_lodscale->value;
192  if (lodscale > 100) lodscale = 100;
193  flod = 1.0f - projectedRadius * lodscale;
194  }
195  else
196  {
197  // object intersects near view plane, e.g. view weapon
198  flod = 0;
199  }
200 
201  flod *= tr.currentModel->numLods;
202  lod = ri.ftol(flod);
203 
204  if ( lod < 0 )
205  {
206  lod = 0;
207  }
208  else if ( lod >= tr.currentModel->numLods )
209  {
210  lod = tr.currentModel->numLods - 1;
211  }
212  }
213 
214  lod += r_lodbias->integer;
215 
216  if ( lod >= tr.currentModel->numLods )
217  lod = tr.currentModel->numLods - 1;
218  if ( lod < 0 )
219  lod = 0;
220 
221  return lod;
222 }
